    <h3 id="requirements">Requirements</h3>
    <p>
        Guacbot requires <a href="http://nodejs.org">Node</a> and a 
        <a href="https://www.mysql.com/downloads/">MySQL</a> database.
    </p>

    <h3 id="quick-start">Quick Start</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <pre>$ git clone https://github.com/prgmrbill/guacbot</pre>
        </li>
        <li>
            <pre>$ npm install</pre>
        </li>
        <li>
            <pre>$ cp bot-config.sample.json bot-config.json</pre>
        </li>
        <li>
            Edit your config - most of the lines at the top are required and self-explanatory.
        </li>
        <li>
            <pre>$ node lib/bot.js</pre>
        </li>
        <li>
            Congratulations! Guacbot is now running. Observe the console output for additional information.
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h3 id="tips">Tips for additional awesomeness</h3>
    <ul class="tips">
        <li>
            Use <a href="//github.com/remy/nodemon">nodemon</a> to automatically restart 
            if the process ends unexpectedly. This shouldn't happen often, though.
        </li>
        <li>
            Use <a href="https://www.gnu.org/software/screen/">screen</a> to keep the process running after you disconnect your session.
        </li>
    </ul>

